639,343

Pertinent to /u/lifeofchrome and possibly others, I changed the requirement to get into the HoP, hopefully to a standard that is more fair than before. 

Previously in order to be featured in the HoP, you'd need to Top 15 of (Hall of Counts or Hall of K Participation) or Top 10 of (Hall of Gets or Hall of 999 or Day's Participated). This meant that you could get into the HoP in several ways but it would not reflect the total participation of the individual.

Instead, I spent the time working on calculating the score of every contributor and from the top 20 scores, those would be featured in the HoP. 

Hopefully that is more fair and reflective than before. This also means that I now have calculated everyone's score if anyone is interested in knowing it (if they are not already in the HoP).
